parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the EPS system can cause the steering wheel to become difficult to turn or seize, making it hard to control the vehicle, which can lead to accidents or loss of control.
symptoms: The power steering warning light illuminates
the steering wheel becomes difficult to turn or seizes
the vehicle is hard to steer
the steering wheel has excessive play
and the airbag light may also illuminate.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the ignition switch can cause the power steering and brakes to become inoperable, making it difficult or impossible to control the vehicle, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The power steering and brakes fail to operate
the check engine warning light illuminates
and the vehicle may stall or lose power.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the steering intermediate shaft can cause the steering wheel to become difficult to turn or seize, making it hard to control the vehicle, which can lead to accidents or loss of control.
